W e can construct a well-formed regular expression to match and extract the link
values from the above text as follows:
href="http://.+?"
Our regular expression looks for strings that start with “href=”http://“,followed
by one or more characters (” .+¿‘), followed by another double quote. The questio n
mark added to the” .+?" indicates that the match is to be done in a “non-greedy”
fashion instead of a “greedy” fashion. A non-greedy match tries to ﬁnd thesmal lest
possible matching string and a greedy match tries to ﬁnd the largest possible
matching string.
W e add parentheses to our regular expression to indicate which part of our matched
string we would like to extract, and produce the following program:
